A leading aspirant for the position of the National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Senator Mohammed Sani Musa paid a visit to the Governor of Gombe State, His Excellency, Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya at the Gombe State Governor’s lodge in Abuja. The visit was in continuation of his consultation with stakeholders and leaders within the party. Senator Sani Musa and Governor Inuwa Yahaya spoke extensively on ways to move the party forward, especially with regards to the March 26 National Convention of the APC.   How can a governor be removed?     Schools shut in Owerri over gunmen’s threat letter     MPC downgrades growth forecast to 3.24 per cent   While presenting his agenda for the party if elected as the national chairman, Senator Sani Musa disclosed that he was fully prepared to bring about a visionary leadership to the APC and rejig the entire party architecture in line with international best practices. In his remarks, Governor Inuwa Yahaya stated that the All Progressives Congress (APC) in all sincerity of purpose deserves the best hand to manage its affairs at this time and he is convinced that Senator Sani Musa posses the right leadership qualities for the job as we head into the National Convention. He urged Senator Sani Musa to continue with his consultations across all the party leaders and prayed for his successful outing at the convention, stressing that he will be looking forward to working with him should he emerge the next national chairman of the APC.